            "metadata": {
                "abstract": "Hundreds of gene expression signatures have been developed during the last two decades. However, due to the multitude of development procedures and sometimes a lack of explanation for their implementation, it can become challenging to apply the original method on custom data. Moreover, at present, there is no unified and tidy interface to compute signature scores with different single sample enrichment methods. For these reasons, we developed hacksig, an R package intended as a unified framework to obtain single sample scores with a tidy output as well as a collection of manually curated gene signatures and methods from cancer transcriptomics literature.",
